        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Build the biga the night before",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "biga",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaqayiu00007gv4bog6crnf"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " ingredients in a bowl until combined. It will be a shaggy, stiff mass. Cover and refrigerate for 10 to 16 hours. By morning it should have roughly doubled, with a web of bubbles visible through the sides.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the final dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Tear the cold biga into rough pieces into the bowl. Add the {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{whole-milk}}, {{yeast-fast-action}}, {{rapeseed-oil}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}}. Mix with your hand or a stand mixer on medium speed for 8 to 10 minutes until the dough is smooth and extensible. It will still be very slack. Cover and rest for 90 minutes at room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fold and proof, 1 hour",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Perform three sets of stretch-and-folds over the first 45 minutes (every 15 minutes). With wet hands, stretch the dough up from one side and fold it over the centre; rotate 90° and repeat three more times per set. After the third set, leave the dough undisturbed for 15 minutes. Line two baking trays with baking paper and dust with flour. Turn the dough out and divide into two pieces without knocking out air. Transfer to the trays, dust the tops with flour, and leave to proof for 1 hour until puffed and jiggly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 22 to 25 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 230°C fan with a baking stone or heavy tray inside and a roasting tray on the shelf below. Carefully slide the ciabatta onto the stone. Throw six ice cubes into the lower tray and close the door. Bake for 22 to 25 minutes until the loaves are deep golden and sound hollow when tapped. Cool on a rack for 30 minutes before tearing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
